fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.views

Interface IDataViewService


  • @SystemService
public interface IDataViewService
    Provides access to data-oriented views for users, including adapted customizations of default views.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent read/write access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • getListViews

        List<IListView> getListViews(ITicket ticket)
        Gets the default list views for an authenticated user from all currently-registered connectors. All instances of IConnector available from the OSGi service registry will be queried.

        The default list contains one view per ISource, either the default provided by the connector, or the default chosen by the user. The default list can be customized by registering instances of IListViewFilter as OSGi services.

        All other persistent variations (customizations for the user) can be obtained using getStoredViews(IListView) and getStoredView(IListView, String).

        Parameters:
        ticket - the non-null ticket for the user to whom the returned list of views belongs.
        Returns:
        gets all list views for a user (no more than one per source). Registered connectors must grant at least the IPermission.READ permission to the user. If no list views are available, this will return an empty list, not null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IListViewFilter, getListViews(ticket,connector)

      • getListViews

        List<IListView> getListViews(ITicket ticket,
                             IConnector connector)
        Gets the default list views for an authenticated user from a specific connector.

        The default list contains one view per ISource, either the default provided by the connector, or the default chosen by the user. The default list can be customized by registering instances of IListViewFilter as OSGi services.

        All other persistent variations (customizations for the user) can be obtained using getStoredViews(IListView) and getStoredView(IListView, String).

        Parameters:
        ticket - the non-null ticket for the user to whom the returned list of views belongs.
        connector - the non-null connector that can provide the data sources used to construct the collection of list views.
        Returns:
        gets all list views for a user (no more than one per source). The connector must grant at least the IPermission.READ permission to the user. If no list views are available, this will return an empty list, not null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IListViewFilter, getListViews(ticket)

      • getStoredViews

        List<IListView> getStoredViews(IListView storedViewsOf)
        Gets all stored views available as variants of the specified list view. Elements in the returned list all share the same owner and the same master source as the specified reference view.
        Parameters:
        storedViewsOf - reference list to evaluate (may be an adapted list).
        Returns:
        the stored variants. May be an empty list, will never be null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getStoredView(IListView, String), IListView.store(String)

      • getStoredView

        IListView getStoredView(IListView storedViewOf,
                        String storedViewName)
        Gets the named stored view for the specified list view. If defined, it will share the same owner and the same master source as the specified reference view.
        Parameters:
        storedViewOf - reference list to evaluate (may be an adapted list).
        storedViewName - name of the required stored view.
        Returns:
        the stored variant, if defined, or null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getStoredViews(IListView), IListView.store(String)

      • importListView

        IListView importListView(InputStream importStream)
                  throws IOException
        Imports a serialized list view definition, to restore an unstored adaptation between user interactions.
        Parameters:
        importStream - source for restoring the definition. The stream will not be closed by this method.
        Returns:
        the restored definition.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurred restoring the definition.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IListView.exportListView(java.io.OutputStream)
